From: Jiasheng Jiang <jiasheng@iscas.ac.cn>
Date: Wed, 22 Dec 2021 15:41:12 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] drivers: net: smc911x: Check for error irq
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.15.12
Git-commit: cb93b3e11d405f20a405a07482d01147ef4934a3

[ Upstream commit cb93b3e11d405f20a405a07482d01147ef4934a3 ]

Because platform_get_irq() could fail and return error irq.
Therefore, it might be better to check it if order to avoid the use of
error irq.

Fixes: ae150435b59e ("smsc: Move the SMC (SMSC) drivers")
Signed-off-by: Jiasheng Jiang <jiasheng@iscas.ac.cn>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/smsc/smc911x.c | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/smsc/smc911x.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/smsc/smc911x.c
index b008b4e8a2a5..0641a1d392b8 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/smsc/smc911x.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/smsc/smc911x.c
@@ -2070,6 +2070,11 @@ static int smc911x_drv_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 
 	ndev->dma = (unsigned char)-1;
 	ndev->irq = platform_get_irq(pdev, 0);
+	if (ndev->irq < 0) {
+		ret = ndev->irq;
+		goto release_both;
+	}
+
 	lp = netdev_priv(ndev);
 	lp->netdev = ndev;
 #ifdef SMC_DYNAMIC_BUS_CONFIG
